Reasoning: The paper discusses the security algorithms of wireless networks, specifically WPA and WPA2, and describes ways of attacking them. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the successful attack on WPA2-PSK and WPA2-Enterprise, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and cyber security (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the progress of the attack and its results, which could fall under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI) as it involves analyzing data and drawing conclusions.
